<br>
I ended up quadding Spectres in OOT. This gave me three fourths of a bubble per pull and pretty damned good money. Probably picked up 300 to 400 pp in the two and a half yellow bubbles I did there.<br>
<br>
It is tricky to quad the spectres and a couple of times I had to gate out, but EXCELLENT exp and loot. The MOBs are high green to low blue. Just make sure you have plenty of bat wings. <p><center><br><font size = 4><font color=yellow><b>"Aces high, Baby...and you just drew the death card."</font></font></b><br><EMBED src="http://freepages.ugo.com/totenkopftz/files/Toten9.swf" quality=high loop=true WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=100 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash" PLUGINSPAGE="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/index.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash"> </EMBED>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulummanaburn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LumManaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/2/01 11:41:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happ</span><hr size=1> I did 47 (48, 49 and 50) in Dreads soloing anything blue by Karnors.  Lots of peeps around to get clarity and SoW to help with downtime. I made a good amount of coin there too, but not from mobs. Ports. Pay attention to the OOC, Shout and Auction channels, there is always someone in dire need of a port who is paying 50-100p.  I got so busy porting peeps one night that I barely had any time to kill stuff.  Of course my bank account got fatter so it was not that bad...<br>
<br>
Anyways back to the mobs. Kill anything that is blue, but stay away from the Ravishing Drolvargs. They have around 4,500 hp (compared to 2,600 on Ragers and Brutes). The spiders will nuke and dot you, but they are weak spells, nothing to worry about. In fact I LOVED it when they would stop chasing me to hit me with their 35 point nuke while I hit them with conflag. Hehe. <br>
